Abubaker Deghayes has two sons killed in Syria . 
  His eldest son Amer is fighting for the organisation Jabhat al-Nusra . 
  He has left his home in Brighton to bring home his other son who is also in the Middle East . 
  His younger sons Abdullah and Jaffar were killed fighting Syrian government forces in separate incidents . 
  Abubaker has not heard from Amer for four weeks and has travelled to Libya to rescue him . 
  He insists he has not 'run away' to join the fight . 
 